<p itemprop="description">An enterprise architect designs and maintains the organisation's target operating model and technology strategy. They work independently to align business strategy with technology capabilities and ensure architectural coherence across the enterprise.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Develop and maintain enterprise architecture frameworks and standards</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Create business capability models and technology roadmaps</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead architecture governance and review processes</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Align technology solutions with business strategy and objectives</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Collaborate with business stakeholders to understand strategic direction</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Provide architecture guidance and mentoring to other architects</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Evaluate emerging technologies and their potential impact</li>
    </ul>
</section>

